<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06164076 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06164076 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PENINSULA; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  The Italian American Heritage Foundation will present its third annual&quot;Introduction to Italian Opera&quot; on Friday in the foundation's cultural centerat 425 N. Fourth St., San Jose.;    Preceded by a cocktail and hors d'oeuvreshour at 7 p.m., the program will consist of arias from operas by Rossini,Donizetti, Puccini and Verdi sung by six members of Opera San Jose.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  FOUNDATION WILL PRESENT OPERA ARIAS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Peninsula Log  </MEMO><TEXT>     After their two-hour performance, pianist Michael Touchi will continue foran additional &quot;open mike&quot; hour in which anyone in the audience can sing. Thoseattending are encouraged to sign up for the session and to have sheet musicwith them.;    Admission costs $15, and tables are available for groups.;  Host families are being sought in Santa Clara County for foreign students whowill be coming here to study under an International Cultural Exchangeprogram.;    Families interested in being hosts or in having an Americanstudent stay with a family abroad should call Michael W. Cox at (415) 735-6936.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Peninsula/AM  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910612  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  163  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday June 12, 199100164076,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>